<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Lining_of_Uterine_Wall.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-=
description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thu=
mb/9/9f/Lining_of_Uterine_Wall.jpg/250px-Lining_of_Uterine_Wall.jpg" decodi=
ng=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=3D"176" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-fi=
le-width=3D"383" data-file-height=3D"269"></a><figcaption>Diagram illustrat=
ing how the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endometrium" title=3D"=
Endometrium">uterine lining</a> builds up and breaks down during the menstr=
ual cycle</figcaption></figure>
<p><b>Menstruation</b> (also known as a <b>period</b>, among other colloqui=
al terms) is the regular discharge of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Blood" title=3D"Blood">blood</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Mucous_membrane" title=3D"Mucous membrane">mucosal tissue</a> from t=
he <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endometrium" title=3D"Endometri=
um">inner lining of the uterus</a> through the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Vagina" title=3D"Vagina">vagina</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Thiyag=
arajan_1-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Me=
nstruation#cite_note-Thiyagarajan-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Menstrual_cycle" title=3D"Menstrual cycle">menstrual cycl=
e</a> is characterized by the rise and fall of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Hormones" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Hormones">hormones</a=
>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Thiyagarajan_1-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Thiyagarajan-1"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 Menstruation is triggered by falling <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Progesterone" title=3D"Progesterone">progesterone</a> levels, and is a =
sign that <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pregnancy" title=3D"Preg=
nancy">pregnancy</a> has not occurred.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Thiyagarajan_1-2"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#=
cite_note-Thiyagarajan-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Feminine_hygiene" title=3D"Feminine hygiene">Feminine hygiene</a> produc=
ts are used in order to maintain hygiene during <b>menses</b>.
</p><p>The first period, a point in time known as <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Menarche" title=3D"Menarche">menarche</a>, usually begins d=
uring <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Puberty" title=3D"Puberty">p=
uberty</a>, between the ages of 11 and 13.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Jones2011_2-0=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation=
#cite_note-Jones2011-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> However, menstruation starting as youn=
g as eight years would still be considered normal.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Women=
2014Men_3-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M=
enstruation#cite_note-Women2014Men-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The average age of the fir=
st period is generally later in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Developing_world" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Developing world">develo=
ping world</a>, and earlier in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Developed_world" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Developed world">developed=
 world</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Diaz2006_4-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Diaz2006-4"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> The typical length of time between the first day of one period and the fi=
rst day of the next is 21 to 45 days in young women; in adults, the range i=
s between 21 and 35 days with the average often cited as 28 days.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-Women2014Men_3-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Women2014Men-3"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-Diaz2006_4-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Diaz2006-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</=
span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In the largest study =
of menstrual app data, the mean menstrual cycle length was determined to be=
 29.3 days.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:6_5-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-:6-5"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Bleeding t=
ypically lasts two to seven days. Periods stop during pregnancy and typical=
ly do not resume during the initial months of <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Breastfeeding" title=3D"Breastfeeding">breastfeeding</a>.<sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-Women2014Men_3-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Women2014Men-3"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lochia" title=3D"Lochia">Lochia</a> occur=
s after childbirth.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-6"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Menstruati=
on, and with it the possibility of pregnancy, ceases after <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menopause" title=3D"Menopause">menopause</a>, whic=
h usually occurs between 45 and 55 years of age.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NIH2013=
Def_7-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menst=
ruation#cite_note-NIH2013Def-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>
During their menstrual period, 38% of all women reported not to be able to =
perform all their regular daily activities.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-The_impact_o=
f_menstrual_symptoms_on_everyday_life:_a_survey_among_42,879_women_8-0" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite=
_note-The_impact_of_menstrual_symptoms_on_everyday_life:_a_survey_among_42,=
879_women-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup> Symptoms in advance of menstruation that do interfe=
re with normal life are called <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pre=
menstrual_syndrome" title=3D"Premenstrual syndrome">premenstrual syndrome</=
a> (PMS). Some 20 to 30% of women experience PMS, with 3 to 8% experiencing=
 severe symptoms.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-AFP2011_9-0" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-AFP2011-9"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup> These include <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acne_vulgaris"=
 class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Acne vulgaris">acne</a>, tender breasts, bl=
oating, feeling tired, irritability, and mood changes.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-W=
omen2014PMS_10-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Menstruation#cite_note-Women2014PMS-10"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Other symptoms some=
 women experience include <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dysmenor=
rhea" title=3D"Dysmenorrhea">painful periods</a> (estimates are between 50 =
and 90%) and heavy bleeding during menstruation and <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Abnormal_uterine_bleeding" title=3D"Abnormal uterine blee=
ding">abnormal bleeding</a> at any time during the menstrual cycle.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-Women2014Men_3-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Women2014Men-3"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> A lack o=
f periods, known as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amenorrhea" ti=
tle=3D"Amenorrhea">amenorrhea</a>, is when periods do not occur by age 15 o=
r have not re-occurred in ninety days.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Women2014Men_3-4"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#=
cite_note-Women2014Men-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></p><div class=3D"toclimit-3"><meta pro=
perty=3D"mw:PageProp/toc"></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Characteristics">Characteri=
stics</h2></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Further information: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstrual_cyc=
le" title=3D"Menstrual cycle">Menstrual cycle</a></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Length_and_duration">Length=
 and duration</h3></div>
<p>The first menstrual period occurs after the onset of pubertal growth, an=
d is called <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menarche" title=3D"Men=
arche">menarche</a>. The average age of menarche is 12 to 15 years.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-Jones2011_2-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Jones2011-2"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menst=
ruation#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> However, it may occur as early as eight.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-Women2014Men_3-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Women2014Men-3"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> =
The average age of the first period is generally later in the <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developing_world" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Developing world">developing world</a>, and earlier in the <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developed_world" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Developed world">developed world</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Diaz2006_4-2" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#c=
ite_note-Diaz2006-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-pmid29778270_12-0" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_n=
ote-pmid29778270-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The average age of menarche has changed li=
ttle in the United States since the 1950s.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Diaz2006_4-3"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#=
cite_note-Diaz2006-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Menstruation is the most visible phase of the <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstrual_cycle" title=3D"Menstrual cycle">menstrual cyc=
le</a> and its beginning is used as the marker between cycles. The first da=
y of menstrual bleeding is the date used for the last menstrual period (LMP=
). The typical length of time between the first day of one period and the f=
irst day of the next is 21 to 45 days in young women, and 21 to 35 days in =
adults.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Women2014Men_3-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Women2014Men-3"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Diaz2006_4-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Diaz2006-4"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The =
average menstrual cycle length is conventionally said to be 28 days.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-Women2014Men_3-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Women2014Men-3"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-Diaz2006_4-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Diaz2006-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In the largest s=
tudy using data from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Period-tracki=
ng_app" title=3D"Period-tracking app">menstrual apps</a>, the mean menstrua=
l cycle length was determined as 29.3 days.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:6_5-1" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_=
note-:6-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> The variability of menstrual cycle lengths is highest=
 for women under 25 years of age and is lowest, that is, most regular, for =
ages 25 to 39 years.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Chiazze1968_13-0" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Chiazze1=
968-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup> The variability increases slightly for women aged 40 to=
 44 years.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Chiazze1968_13-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Chiazze1968-13"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perimenopause" class=3D"mw-=
redirect" title=3D"Perimenopause">Perimenopause</a> refers to the transitio=
nal phase leading up to menopause, marked by hormonal changes and irregular=
 menstrual cycles, when a woman stops menstruating completely and is no lon=
ger fertile. The medical definition of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Menopause" title=3D"Menopause">menopause</a> is one year without a per=
iod and typically occurs between 45 and 55 years in Western countries.<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-NIH2013Def_7-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-NIH2013Def-7"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-Carlson_2004_14-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Carlson_2004-14"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=
=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Page / location: 381">:=E2=80=8A381=E2=
=80=8A</span></sup> Menopause before age 45 is considered <i>premature</i> =
in industrialized countries.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-15"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> Illnesses, certain surgeries, or medical treatments may cause menopause t=
o occur earlier than it might have otherwise.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-pmid310276=
83_16-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menst=
