ection is an excerpt from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstrua=
l_cycle#Menstrual_health" title=3D"Menstrual cycle">Menstrual cycle =C2=A7 =
Menstrual health</a>.<span class=3D"mw-editsection-like plainlinks"><span c=
lass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a class=3D"external text" href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DMenstrual_cycle&amp;action=3De=
dit">edit</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div><d=
iv class=3D"excerpt">
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Human_ovarian_follicle.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-=
description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thu=
mb/c/ca/Human_ovarian_follicle.jpg/250px-Human_ovarian_follicle.jpg" decodi=
ng=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=3D"142" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-fi=
le-width=3D"2517" data-file-height=3D"1430"></a><figcaption>A human primary=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ovarian_follicle" title=3D"Ovaria=
n follicle">ovarian follicle</a> viewed by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Microscopy" title=3D"Microscopy">microscopy</a>. The round <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oocyte" title=3D"Oocyte">oocyte</a> stain=
ed red in the center is surrounded by a layer of <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Granulosa_cell" title=3D"Granulosa cell">granulosa cells</a>=
, which are enveloped by the basement membrane and <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Theca_cell" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Theca cell">the=
ca cells</a>. The magnification is around 1000 times. (<a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/H%26E_stain" title=3D"H&amp;E stain">H&amp;E stain</a>=
)</figcaption></figure>
<p>Although a normal and natural process,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEPrior2=
02050_23-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Me=
nstruation#cite_note-FOOTNOTEPrior202050-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[=
</span>23<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> some women experie=
nce <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Premenstrual_syndrome" title=
=3D"Premenstrual syndrome">premenstrual syndrome</a> with symptoms that may=
 include <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acne_vulgaris" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Acne vulgaris">acne</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Breast_tenderness" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Breast tender=
ness">tender breasts</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fati=
gue" title=3D"Fatigue">tiredness</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Menstrual_cycle_pm=
id32809533_24-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Menstruation#cite_note-Menstrual_cycle_pmid32809533-24"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>24<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> More=
  severe symptoms that affect daily living are classed as <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Premenstrual_dysphoric_disorder" title=3D"Premenstr=
ual dysphoric disorder">premenstrual dysphoric disorder</a> and are experie=
nced by 3 to 8% of women.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Menstrual_cycle_Reed2018_25-0"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#=
cite_note-Menstrual_cycle_Reed2018-25"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>25<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Menst=
rual_cycle_pmid29298169_26-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Menstrual_cycle_pmid29298169-26"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>26<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Menstrual_cycle_pmid32809533_24-1" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Men=
strual_cycle_pmid32809533-24"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>24<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Menstrual_cycl=
e_pmid33030880_27-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Menstrual_cycle_pmid33030880-27"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>27<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
  <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dysmenorrhea" title=3D"Dysmenorr=
hea">Dysmenorrhea</a> (menstrual cramps or period pain) is felt as painful =
cramps in the abdomen that can spread to the back and upper thighs during t=
he first few days of menstruation.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Menstrual_cycle_nhs1_=
28-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstrua=
tion#cite_note-Menstrual_cycle_nhs1-28"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>28<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Mens=
trual_cycle_Dysmenorrheastat_29-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Menstrual_cycle_Dysmenorrheasta=
t-29"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>29<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]=
</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Menstrual_cycle_pmid30098748_30-0" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite=
_note-Menstrual_cycle_pmid30098748-30"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>30<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Debilitating period pain=
 is not normal and can be a sign of something severe such as <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endometriosis" title=3D"Endometriosis">endometri=
osis</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Menstrual_cycle_pmid33132854_31-0" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Me=
nstrual_cycle_pmid33132854-31"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>31<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> These issues can significantly a=
ffect a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Women%27s_health" title=3D=
"Women's health">woman's health</a> and quality of life and timely interven=
tions can improve the lives of these women.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Menstrual_cy=
cle_pmid31378287_32-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-Menstrual_cycle_pmid31378287-32"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
>
</p>
There are common culturally communicated misbeliefs that the menstrual cycl=
e affects women's moods, causes depression or irritability, or that menstru=
ation is a painful, shameful or unclean experience. Often a woman's normal =
mood variation is falsely attributed to the menstrual cycle. Much of the re=
search is weak, but there appears to be a very small increase in mood fluct=
uations during the luteal and menstrual phases, and a corresponding decreas=
e during the rest of the cycle.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEElse-QuestHyde20=
21258=E2=80=93261_33-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_note-FOOTNOTEElse-QuestHyde2021258%E2%80%93261-=
33"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>33<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup> Changing levels of estrogen and progesterone across the men=
strual cycle exert systemic effects on aspects of physiology including the =
brain, metabolism, and musculoskeletal system. The result can be subtle phy=
siological and observable changes to women's athletic performance including=
 strength, aerobic, and anaerobic performance.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-34" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menstruation#cite_n=
ote-34"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>34<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup></div></div>
